author: EVAN GRICE Sports Editor
title: Gainesville High School soccer releases 2015-16 season schedules
text:
Gainesville High School soccer releases 2015-16 season schedules By EVAN GRICE Sports Editor gainesvilleregister.com 
Coming off the most successful campaign in program history which saw both teams make the regional quarterfinals, the Gainesville High School boys and girls soccer teams released their schedules for the upcoming 2015-16 season earlier this week. 
The Lady Leopards will begin their season Jan. 2 with a pair of scrimmages against Irving and Grand Prairie, before taking part in the Richland Rebels Winter Blast Tournament beginning on Jan. 7. 
The following week will see the Lady Leopards take part in the Aledo Tournament of Champions tournament. 
GHS will host the Big Red Classic on Jan. 21-23, along with having home games on Feb. 5 against Diamond Hill Jarvis, and Feb. 9 against Celina. 
Meanwhile the Leopards will have an alumni game on Jan. 2 before taking part in the Crowley Tournament on Jan. 7. 
Home games against Kemp and Frisco Reedy will then follow on Jan. 9 and Jan. 12, before the Leopards will travel to the Burkburnett Tournament on Jan. 15.
